ExamFlow Phase 1 MVP Build Prompt

1. Phase Objective
Build the first production-ready MVP of ExamFlow with the smallest useful feature set that still delivers a complete study and practice experience.

The MVP should prove that users can:
- Sign up and log in.
- Select an exam.
- Study structured learning content.
- Attempt quizzes and mock tests.
- Track progress.
- Save bookmarks and notes.
- Access a basic admin workflow for content management.

2. MVP Scope
Include only the features required to launch a strong core product.

Must-have user features:
- Authentication.
- Onboarding.
- Exam selection.
- Syllabus browsing.
- Topic reading.
- Question practice.
- Mock tests.
- Test scoring.
- Progress tracking.
- Bookmarks.
- Notes.
- Search.
- Notifications.

Must-have admin features:
- Dashboard.
- User management.
- Content management.
- Question management.
- Test management.
- Basic moderation.
- Analytics overview.

3. What Not To Build Yet
Do not include in Phase 1:
- Advanced AI tutor.
- Full community contribution workflow.
- Complex recommendation engine.
- Subscription billing.
- Multi-language expansion beyond basic support.
- Heavy personalization.
- Offline sync complexity beyond simple caching.
- Deep social features.

4. Phase 1 Product Goal
The goal is to launch a stable, clear, and useful exam-prep app that users can actually study with and that the team can operate efficiently.

5. Phase 1 Deliverables
- Flutter mobile app MVP.
- Backend API MVP.
- Admin panel MVP.
- MySQL schema and seed data.
- Basic content workflows.
- Basic tests and analytics tracking.
- Deployment-ready structure.

6. Phase 1 Functional Requirements
A. Authentication
- Register.
- Login.
- Logout.
- Password reset.
- Session refresh.
- Secure token storage.

B. Onboarding
- Choose exam.
- Choose language.
- Choose preparation goal.
- Load initial syllabus.

C. Learning
- Display exam hierarchy.
- Show subjects, chapters, and topics.
- Render textbook-style content.
- Support bookmarking and highlights.
- Track topic completion.

D. Practice
- Load quiz questions by topic.
- Show one question at a time or in a list.
- Submit answers.
- Show explanations.
- Record attempt history.

E. Tests
- Start a mock test.
- Track timer.
- Save answers.
- Submit test.
- Calculate score.
- Show result breakdown.
- Show weak topics.

F. Revision
- Show saved content.
- Show recently viewed topics.
- Show weak topics.
- Show incorrect question review.

G. Progress
- Track topic completion.
- Track test performance.
- Track streaks.
- Show learning dashboard.

H. Bookmarks and Notes
- Save content.
- Save personal notes.
- Edit and delete notes.
- Access saved items later.

I. Search
- Search exams, topics, and questions.
- Show filtered results.
- Allow quick navigation to content.

J. Notifications
- In-app notifications.
- Basic push notification support.
- Admin-generated announcements.

7. MVP Admin Requirements
A. Dashboard
- Show user count.
- Show content count.
- Show test count.
- Show pending content.
- Show basic engagement metrics.

B. Content Management
- Create and edit learning content.
- Publish or unpublish content.
- Map content to topics.

C. Question Management
- Create and edit questions.
- Add explanations.
- Tag by subject and topic.
- Publish questions to quizzes and tests.

D. Test Management
- Create quizzes and mock tests.
- Attach questions.
- Set timing and scoring.
- Publish tests.

E. User Management
- View users.
- Block users if needed.
- Review activity.

F. Moderation
- Review community submissions if enabled lightly.
- Approve or reject content.

8. MVP Build Order
Build in this order:
1. Authentication.
2. Exam selection and syllabus structure.
3. Content reading screens.
4. Question practice.
5. Test engine.
6. Progress tracking.
7. Bookmarks and notes.
8. Search.
9. Admin panel.
10. Analytics and notifications.
11. Final QA and deployment.

9. Mobile App Build Tasks
- Set up Flutter project structure.
- Implement routing.
- Build auth screens.
- Build onboarding screens.
- Build home dashboard.
- Build syllabus browser.
- Build content reader.
- Build practice flow.
- Build test flow.
- Build results screen.
- Build bookmarks and notes UI.
- Build progress screens.
- Build search screen.
- Connect API integration layer.
- Add local caching.
- Add error states and loading states.

10. Backend Build Tasks
- Set up auth and roles.
- Create exam, subject, chapter, and topic tables.
- Create content and question APIs.
- Create test and attempt APIs.
- Create progress and bookmark APIs.
- Create admin CRUD APIs.
- Create search endpoints.
- Add analytics event capture.
- Add notification support.
- Add moderation logic if needed.

11. API Priorities
Implement first:
- Auth.
- Exams.
- Syllabus.
- Content.
- Questions.
- Tests.
- Progress.
- Bookmarks.
- Notes.
- Admin CRUD.

12. Database Priorities
Implement first:
- users.
- user_profiles.
- exams.
- subjects.
- chapters.
- topics.
- learning_contents.
- questions.
- tests.
- test_questions.
- test_attempts.
- test_attempt_answers.
- bookmarks.
- notes.
- progress.

13. Acceptance Criteria
The MVP is successful if:
- A new user can sign up and start studying within minutes.
- A user can complete a mock test and see results.
- Progress is tracked correctly.
- Admin can publish content and questions.
- The app remains stable and fast on mobile.

14. Quality Standards
- No broken navigation paths.
- No missing empty states.
- No uncaught API errors.
- No content without metadata.
- No test scoring inconsistencies.
- No unauthorized admin access.

15. Recommended Phase 1 Milestones
Milestone 1: Project setup and auth.
Milestone 2: Syllabus and content reading.
Milestone 3: Practice and tests.
Milestone 4: Progress and bookmarks.
Milestone 5: Admin panel.
Milestone 6: QA and launch.

16. Phase 1 Summary
This phase should prove the core product loop: learn, practice, test, and improve.

